other_tests.findings: Fetal heart rate was 140 beats per minute, with moderate variability, accelerations, and a single deceleration with a rapid return to baseline.
Right ventricular dilatation indicating acute right ventricular failure and moderate tricuspid regurgitation. After treatment, right ventricular function improved, and dilation decreased.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Dilatation in right ventricle decreased from moderate-to-severe impairment to mild impairment after treatment with inotropic agents and inhaled nitric oxide.
